					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Records, in Sanskrit verse written in Grantha characters, the various gifts to the deity and the gilding of several parts of the temple from out of the gold of the second <hi rend="italic">Tulābhāra</hi> ceremony performed by the king <hi rend="bold">Sundara Pāṇḍya</hi> and alludes to his victories over Siṁhaṇa and Rāma of the Hoysaḷa dynasty, the Chēras and the Chōḷas. The king may be identified with <hi rend="bold">Jaṭāvarmaṉ Sundara Pāṇḍya I</hi> who bore the epithet <hi rend="bold">Poṉmēynda-Perumāḷ</hi> or <hi rend="bold">Hēmāchchādanarāja.</hi></p>						

						<p>(Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. IV, No. 507)</p>						

						</summary>
